349
00:13:48,125 --> 00:13:50,541
You can't tell me
because you have no idea!

350
00:13:50,625 --> 00:13:52,375
Stop making excuses!

351
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:55,958
Oh, yeah!
Like you know anything!

352
00:13:56,041 --> 00:13:57,750
You don't even know
what this movie's about!

353
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,625
How dare you make
selfish demands?!

354
00:13:59,708 --> 00:14:01,500
You're the one who's
being selfish here!

355
00:14:01,583 --> 00:14:03,875
You're just hitting Miss
Asahina because you want to!

356
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,416
How dare you
treat her like that?!

357
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,958
Don't you talk to me like that!

358
00:14:07,041 --> 00:14:08,416
Who do you think you are?!

359
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:11,250
This is called "story" and
it's important for my movie!

360
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:12,041
Get it now?!

361
00:14:12,125 --> 00:14:13,541
It's not important!

362
00:14:13,625 --> 00:14:15,166
Know what?! This sucks!

363
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:16,958
Miss Asahina is not your toy!

364
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:18,875
Shut up! It's important to me!

365
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:21,291
And I can treat her
like a toy if I want to!

366
00:14:21,375 --> 00:14:22,541
[growls]

367
00:14:26,583 --> 00:14:28,250
[BOTH gasp]

368
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:42,666
[HARUHI]
Wha-What is it?!

369
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,791
What is your problem
anyway, huh?!

370
00:14:44,875 --> 00:14:46,875
You just have to do
what I tell you!

371
00:14:46,958 --> 00:14:50,208
I'm the brigade leader!
I'm the director!

372
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:55,500
Whatever!

373
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:58,000
Do what I say or get out!

374
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:05,916
[KYON]
Let go, Koizumi!

375
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,708
I don't care if it's
a person or an animal,

376
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:10,541
if they won't listen,
they deserved to be smacked!

377
00:15:10,625 --> 00:15:12,166
If she doesn't learn
her lesson now,

378
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:15,000
she's gonna grow up to be
some kind of lonely freak!

379
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:17,291
[MIKURU]
Stop it! Don't!

380
00:15:19,583 --> 00:15:22,375
Stop fighting... Stop it!

381
00:15:22,458 --> 00:15:28,000
Or else... Nevermind,
it's classified anyway...

382
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:39,958
[TSURUYA]
I'm sorry, Kyon.

383
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:42,083
I got a little carried away.

384
00:15:44,875 --> 00:15:46,750
You don't have
to worry about Mikuru.

385
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:49,125
I'll take her home
or have her stay the night.

386
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:55,750
I always thought of you
as being more rational

387
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:57,291
than you were back there.

388
00:15:57,375 --> 00:15:59,375
[KYON]
Yeah, so did I.

389
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:02,208
The good news is that
closed space hasn't appeared.

390
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:04,208
It looks like Miss
Suzumiya's subconscious

391
00:16:04,291 --> 00:16:06,250
was able to control
itself this time.

392
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,708
[KYON]
Awesome. Less work for you.

393
00:16:08,791 --> 00:16:10,916
[KOIZUMI]
By the way, if you're free,

394
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,375
there's a place
I'd like to take you to.

395
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:15,625
And what if I said no?

396
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:17,791
I don't think this
should take too long.

397
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:23,458
[KOIZUMI] Do you remember what
Miss Suzumiya said yesterday?

398
00:16:23,541 --> 00:16:28,250
How am I supposed to remember
all the crazy stuff she says?

399
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:31,375
When you see this, I'm sure
it'll come back to you.

400
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:34,458
I think they've been like that
ever since this morning.

401
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:41,541
Did someone come out here and
paint 'em all or something?

402
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:44,000
No, that's the natural coloring
of their feathers.

403
00:16:44,083 --> 00:16:45,375
There's no mistaking it.

404
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:47,458
Well, maybe all
the gunfire yesterday

405
00:16:47,541 --> 00:16:48,875
scared the heck out of 'em.

406
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:51,375
Even if that were
really the case,

407
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:53,458
do you think this is
what would happen?

408
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:55,041
[KYON]
Yeah, I know.

409
00:16:55,125 --> 00:16:58,000
[HARUHI] It would be so awesome
if the pigeons were all white,

410
00:16:58,083 --> 00:17:01,250
but I guess it doesn't matter
what color they are.

411
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:02,916
[KYON]
Apparently, it did.

412
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,125
Here's my perspective
on the situation.

413
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:06,666
Miss Suzumiya's special.

414
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:08,250
However, at one point,

415
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:11,458
she was given her godlike powers
by someone or something else.

416
00:17:11,541 --> 00:17:14,041
Ultimately, she's just an
ordinary human being,

417
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:15,791
as opposed to a divine being.

418
00:17:15,875 --> 00:17:18,291
Her presence in this world
is proof of that.

419
00:17:18,375 --> 00:17:20,541
Well, that's a
new spin on things.

420
00:17:20,625 --> 00:17:22,125
Correct me if I'm wrong,

421
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:23,416
but didn't you say
something before

422
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,125
about how Haruhi
was a god?

423
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:26,833
Really? Did I say that?

424
00:17:26,916 --> 00:17:28,500
[KYON]
Don't mess with me.

425
00:17:28,583 --> 00:17:30,583
Of course I'm only kidding.

426
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:33,666
Miss Suzumiya is the one who
can create the world around us.

427
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:36,500
And at the same time,
she can destroy it.

428
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:38,375
Perhaps the reality
we're currently in

429
00:17:38,458 --> 00:17:41,041
isn't working as
efficiently as it should.

430
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:42,375
And perhaps the only person

431
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:45,000
who has the power to fix
this failed world of ours

432
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:47,750
is the one we've come
to know as Miss Suzumiya.

433
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:49,083
[KYON]
Yeah, sure.

434
00:17:49,166 --> 00:17:50,333
[KOIZUMI]
Consider this:

435
00:17:50,416 --> 00:17:52,166
If she's creating all this
strange phenomena

436
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:54,125
to fix whatever's wrong
with the world,

437
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:55,833
then our attempts
at covering it up

438
00:17:55,916 --> 00:17:58,666
might be preventing that
change from taking place.

439
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:00,958
[KYON]
Hmph. So what?

440
00:18:01,041 --> 00:18:02,791
[KOIZUMI] It means we
could be in a lot of trouble,

441
00:18:02,875 --> 00:18:04,208
that's what.

442
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:05,833
When Miss Suzumiya
changes this world

443
00:18:05,916 --> 00:18:09,041
to a version that's
functioning properly,

444
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:11,125
do you think there would
still be a need for us

445
00:18:11,208 --> 00:18:13,375
and our special abilities?

446
00:18:13,458 --> 00:18:15,791
Or, will we be considered
the bugs in the program

447
00:18:15,875 --> 00:18:17,041
and exterminated?

448
00:18:17,125 --> 00:18:18,875
[KYON]
Who knows?

449
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:21,875
Honestly, with all its faults,

450
00:18:21,958 --> 00:18:23,875
I like the world the way it is.

451
00:18:23,958 --> 00:18:27,375
It's been built piece by piece
by so many different people,

452
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:30,458
from ancient times
to the present.

453
00:18:30,541 --> 00:18:34,000
If I had my way, I wouldn't
change a single thing about it.

454
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:36,333
That's why I do what
I can about Miss Suzumiya

455
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:38,500
and the situations
she puts us in.

456
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,083
I wonder if this world
is really worth

457
00:18:40,166 --> 00:18:41,666
all the trouble
you're going through.

458
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:42,750
Oh?

459
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:44,833
I thought you of
all people felt it was.

460
00:18:44,916 --> 00:18:46,000
Otherwise, you
wouldn't have come back

461
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:48,458
from closed space that one time.

462
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:50,166
Or am I mistaken?

463
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,416
Well, who knows? I don't.

464
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,375
It's out of character for me
to be so presumptuous.

465
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:03,500
And for a second there,

466
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:04,875
I might've sounded
like I was inferring

467
00:19:04,958 --> 00:19:07,250
that we were the
protectors of this world.

468
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,791
Please forgive me.

469
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:28,000
[KOIZUMI]
Rather than being angry today,

470
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:31,250
it seems Miss Suzumiya
is too busy feeling sad.

471
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:33,541
[KYON]
Really? Why's that?

472
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:36,250
[KOIZUMI] I thought you
of all people would know why.

473
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,166
I don't mind
explaining it, though.

474
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:40,958
Miss Suzumiya always thought
that no matter what happened,

475
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:43,500
you'd be right there,
by her side,

476
00:19:43,583 --> 00:19:45,875
even though you'd
sometimes complain.

477
00:19:45,958 --> 00:19:48,250
You alone would forgive her.

478
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:50,541
[KYON] Yeah, well, the only one
who could forgive her now

479
00:19:50,625 --> 00:19:52,375
would be a martyred saint.

480
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:53,708
[KOIZUMI] Do you think
you could say something

481
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:56,000
to Miss Suzumiya
to cheer her up?

482
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:58,625
If you don't, she might
continue to get depressed.

483
00:19:58,708 --> 00:20:02,250
And then something much worse
than closed space could appear.

484
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:03,416
I don't even want to think about

485
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:05,375
what would happen
to the world if...

486
00:20:05,458 --> 00:20:08,875
...well, if she were to sink
into a deep depression.

487
00:20:08,958 --> 00:20:11,291
[KYON] So, you're telling me
to go cheer her up.

488
00:20:11,375 --> 00:20:13,833
[KOIZUMI] You just need to get
back together with her again.

489
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:15,875
[KYON] Yeah, see,
that's where you're wrong.

490
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,958
I was never "with her"
to begin with.

491
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:19,500
[KOIZUMI]
Oh, well...

492
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:22,000
I thought that you would've
cooled off a bit more by now.

493
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:24,291
I guess I was wrong.

494
00:20:24,375 --> 00:20:25,958
[KYON] The reason
I got so angry yesterday

495
00:20:26,041 --> 00:20:27,500
was because I couldn't
stand watching

496
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:31,083
Miss Asahina getting abused
and degraded like that.

497
00:20:31,166 --> 00:20:33,833
But that's not the only reason.

498
00:20:33,916 --> 00:20:37,833
I could've been suffering
from calcium deficiency.

499
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:41,583
So, before bed last night,
I downed a liter of milk.

500
00:20:41,666 --> 00:20:44,083
And it seemed to
calm me down a little bit.

501
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:46,833
It... could've been
a placebo effect, though.

502
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:50,125
[TANIGUCHI]
Yeah, movie, what a joke.

503
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,416
[KUNIKIDA]
Don't listen to him.

504
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,791
He's just upset
'cause he wanted to

505
00:20:52,875 --> 00:20:55,291
hang out with you guys
and Miss Suzumiya some more.

506
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:57,625
He even cancelled
his plans on that day.

507
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:59,375
Don't tell him that, you jerk!

508
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:01,291
So anyway, you can
just forget about

509
00:21:01,375 --> 00:21:04,208
me helping out on any more
of your stupid projects.

510
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:05,958
Movie... yeah, right.

511
00:21:06,041 --> 00:21:07,958
Nobody's gonna watch that trash!

512
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:08,708
For real.

513
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:10,083
[KYON growls]

514
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:12,916
You're the last person
I wanna hear that from.

515
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,250
[TANIGUCHI]
Hm?

516
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:16,333
[KYON] It's not like I
can't imagine it, though.

517
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:20,041
But hearing a guy like him
say it really pisses me off.

518
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:21,541
At least Haruhi's
doing something

519
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:22,833
for the school festival.

520
00:21:22,916 --> 00:21:24,333
She's trying to get involved.

521
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:26,791
Can you say the same
about yourself?

522
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,291
Who cares if it's stupid?!

523
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:29,916
At least she's trying
to make something.

524
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,041
Look at you!

525
00:21:31,125 --> 00:21:33,041
You're just sitting
there complaining!

526
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,458
Man... That really
pisses me off!

527
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:39,791
Why am I so angry
about it though?

528
00:21:39,875 --> 00:21:40,958
I wonder...

529
00:21:41,041 --> 00:21:42,458
Is it because I've
suddenly found a passion

530
00:21:42,541 --> 00:21:45,125
for making movies or something?

531
00:21:45,208 --> 00:21:47,333
Is there something wrong, Kyon?

532
00:21:47,416 --> 00:21:49,541
Miss Suzumiya looked upset, too.

533
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:51,125
Did something happen?

534
00:21:51,208 --> 00:21:54,000
[TANIGUCHI]
Lovers' spat, whatever.

535
00:21:54,083 --> 00:21:55,166
[KYON]
Hmph.

536
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:56,583
I get it now.

537
00:21:56,666 --> 00:21:58,000
I do what Haruhi tells me to do,

538
00:21:58,083 --> 00:22:00,208
and then I go out
and complain about it.

539
00:22:00,291 --> 00:22:02,708
There's no difference
between me and Taniguchi.

540
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:05,333
I mean, I got so mad at the
stuff he was saying just now,

541
00:22:05,416 --> 00:22:08,541
but how's it any different
from what I've said before?!

542
00:22:08,625 --> 00:22:11,166
Dammit! Taniguchi, you bastard!

543
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,583
Thanks to you,
I've realized something

544
00:22:12,666 --> 00:22:14,541
and I'm not happy about it!

545
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:17,500
And now, I'm gonna go do
something I know I'll regret!

546
00:22:17,583 --> 00:22:20,750
Dammit... Dammit! Dammit!

547
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:22,125
[HARUHI gasps]

548
00:22:30,041 --> 00:22:32,541
Hey, Haruhi.

549
00:22:32,625 --> 00:22:34,916
What do you want?

550
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,750
We're gonna finish this movie,
and it's gonna be awesome.

551
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:38,875
[HARUHI gasps]

552
00:22:45,708 --> 00:22:46,666
[chuckles]

553
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:49,708
Well of course, it will!

554
00:22:49,791 --> 00:22:52,041
I am the director, after all.

555
00:22:52,125 --> 00:22:54,791
Everyone knows it's
gonna be awesome.

556
00:22:54,875 --> 00:22:57,291
I certainly don't need
you to tell me that.

557
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:59,833
[KYON]
Man, talk about a mood swing.

558
00:22:59,916 --> 00:23:02,666
Oh, well. Things get weird
when Haruhi's grumpy,

559
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:04,375
so I guess this
really is for the best.

560
00:23:04,458 --> 00:23:06,041
Here we go!

561
00:23:10,875 --> 00:23:12,041
You could've at least

562
00:23:12,125 --> 00:23:13,958
tried to pick a better way
to say it to her.

563
00:23:14,041 --> 00:23:15,041
Sorry.

564
00:23:15,125 --> 00:23:17,083
Not only is she back
to her old self,

565
00:23:17,166 --> 00:23:19,333
now she's even more
powerful than ever!

566
00:23:19,416 --> 00:23:21,000
Sorry.

567
00:23:21,083 --> 00:23:23,833
We won't be able to cover things
up for much longer.

568
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,666
Can you believe
how perfect this is?!

569
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:32,458
I was just thinking about a
scene with cherry blossoms!

570
00:23:32,541 --> 00:23:35,833
This weird weather came along
right at the nick of time!

571
00:23:35,916 --> 00:23:37,666
Let me see your victory pose!

572
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:38,541
[MIKURU]
Huh?

573
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:40,500
[whimpers]

574
00:23:40,583 --> 00:23:41,375
I know!

575
00:23:41,458 --> 00:23:42,958
We need to find ourselves a cat!

576
00:23:43,041 --> 00:23:44,166
A cat?

577
00:23:44,250 --> 00:23:46,125
Yeah. Every witch
needs a familiar, right?

578
00:23:46,208 --> 00:23:48,333
And nothing says
familiar like a cat!

579
00:23:48,416 --> 00:23:50,750
I wonder if there's
a black cat around here.

580
00:23:50,833 --> 00:23:52,041
Wasn't Nagato supposed to be

581
00:23:52,125 --> 00:23:54,333
playing an evil alien
in this thing?

582
00:23:54,416 --> 00:23:55,750
You and your details.

583
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:58,500
I need a cat for this movie,
so let's find one!

584
00:23:58,583 --> 00:23:59,666
How 'bout it, Yuki?

585
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:00,916
Do you know any
place around here

586
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,958
where we can find
a buncha stray cats?

